            <Title>Noting</Title>
            <Text>Earlier we said that vipassana is the process of continually noticing your experience and the sensations that it comprises. One way to do this is with the *noting technique*, where you use one word labels to describe whatever you’re experiencing. Every few seconds, you name whatever is taking center stage in that moment and note it silently or aloud.

Turtle: Sound confusing? We’ll demonstrate in just a second!</Text>
