            <Title>Meditation comprises a variety of techniques that target</Title>
            <Text>Meditation comprises a variety of techniques that target the functioning of the mind. It can lead to profound perceptual and cognitive transformations that have traditonally been called spiritual enlightenment or awakening.

Turtle: It might be more accurate to say *enlightenments* or *awaken-ing*, since the results of meditation are neither uniform nor steady state. </Text>
        </Document>
        <Document ID="5">
            <Title>Meditation can make you feel good, but it can also</Title>
            <Text>Meditation can make you feel good, but it can also be boring, stressful, and frustrating at times.

Turtle: It’s not a linear development of feeling better and better. </Text>
